Generates the base configuration for spawning a thread, from which
configuration methods can be chained.

# Examples

```
use std::thread;

let builder = thread::Builder::new()
                              .name("foo".into())
                              .stack_size(32 * 1024);

let handler = builder.spawn(|| {
    // thread code
}).unwrap();

handler.join().unwrap();
```
